# Phase 3 R7: Form A-K (Hybrid OPD with Rao-Blackwellized future), K=2
#
# Math:
#   A_t = -kl_coef * (c_t + γ * d_K(h_{t+1})) / actual_k     (mean agg, K=2 → divide by 2 unless t=T-1)
#     c_t   = log π_S(y_t|h_t) - log π_T(y_t|h_t)            (sampled, action-specific)
#     d_K(h_{t+1}) = KL(π̂_S(·|h_{t+1}) ‖ π̂_T(·|h_{t+1}))    over teacher top-K=20 support
#                   with renormalization within the support set (paper Eq. 7)
#
# Reference: arXiv 2603.25562 (Revisiting OPD) §3 — teacher top-K local support matching.
#
# Mathematical status (per ChatGPT review):
#   - Unbiased estimator of ∇J(θ) ONLY under: full-vocab d (no top-K), γ=1, K=∞, on-policy, no clip.
#   - This config (K=2, top-K=20, γ=1, PPO clip) is a BIASED SURROGATE of J. We are
#     optimizing a truncated reverse-KL objective J_K, equivalently the unbiased
#     gradient of J_K (within paper §3.1's truncated-support definition).
#   - Variance: RB future removes conditional variance of future token rewards given
#     prefix; per-position L2 strictly decreases vs sampled. Cross-position covariance
#     is not strictly bounded — global variance dominance NOT guaranteed.
#
# Comparison vs R1 (mean K=8 sampled cumulative, our Phase 2.5 winner):
#   - R7 changes: K (8→2), j>=1 estimator (sampled c → top-K renorm d_K), all else same
#   - Tests two hypotheses jointly:
#       (a) Even with shorter horizon (K=2), RB future is strong enough to match/beat R1
#       (b) Top-K renormalized d_K supplies meaningful chunk-level signal beyond sampled c
#
# Setup: 4B Full FT v2 ckpt-700 student (60% AIME baseline) + Qwen3-8B teacher EXT (qzf-dev)

MODEL_CONFIG=qwen3-4B
STUDENT_HF=/root/.cache/huggingface/sft-qwen3-4b-full-v2-ckpt700
STUDENT_TORCH_DIST=/root/.cache/huggingface/sft-qwen3-4b-full-v2-ckpt700-torch_dist
TEACHER_HF=/root/.cache/huggingface/Qwen3-8B
TRAIN_DATA=/workspace/data/dapo-math-17k/dapo-math-17k.jsonl
SAVE_DIR=/root/.cache/huggingface/opd-4b-R7-formA-K2

# External teacher (qzf-dev DP=4 Qwen3-8B)
EXTERNAL_TEACHER_URL="http://172.31.31.105:30000/generate"
EXTERNAL_TEACHER_HEALTH="http://172.31.31.105:30000/health_generate"
ACTOR_GPUS=4
ACTOR_TP=4
ROLLOUT_GPUS=4

# Match opd-4b-B paper recipe (same as R1)
LR=2e-6
NUM_ROLLOUT=300
ROLLOUT_BATCH_SIZE=64
GLOBAL_BATCH_SIZE=256
N_SAMPLES=4
MAX_RESPONSE_LEN=4096
OPD_KL_COEF=1.0
SAVE_INTERVAL=50
TEMPERATURE=0.8
TOP_P=1.0
TOP_K=-1

# FAST throughput knobs (R1-confirmed safe values for 4B + ext teacher)
MAX_TOKENS_PER_GPU=16384
LOG_PROBS_MAX_TOKENS_PER_GPU=24576
RECOMPUTE=0

# Cumulative OPD: K=2 mean, gamma=1.0
# (mean ÷ actual_k matches R1's normalization; effectively kl_coef ÷ K interior)
OPD_CUMULATIVE=1
OPD_GAMMA=1.0
OPD_HORIZON=2
OPD_AGG=mean

# Form A-K: enable RB future (j>=1 sampled c → top-K renormalized d_K)
OPD_FUTURE_RB=1
OPD_FUTURE_TOPK=20
OPD_FUTURE_NO_RENORM=0

# KL dump every 10 rollouts for offline analysis (now also captures token_ids)
OPD_DUMP_KL_PATH=/root/.cache/huggingface/opd-4b-R7-formA-K2/kl_dump/r{rollout_id}_rank{rank}.jsonl
OPD_DUMP_KL_INTERVAL=10
OPD_DUMP_KL_MAX_SAMPLES=8
